   <!-- Tool Usage
    ================================================== -->
         
        <div class="gray-bg"> <!-- fullwidth gray background -->
            <br> <br><br><br><br><br>
            <div class="container"><!-- container -->
                <div class="row"> <!-- row -->
                    <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="panel panel-default">
                    <div class="panel-heading magenta">
                        <h4 class="center"><strong> TOOL USAGE </strong></h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel-body black">
                        <h4> <strong><i class="fa fa-hand-o-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; INSTRUCTIONS :</strong></h4><br>
                         <li><i class="fa fa-crosshairs" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; 
                            Go through the pdf files  in the above section for understanding data , make sure you go through the datatypes of those files and understand what the numericals mean .
                         </li>
                         <li><i class="fa fa-crosshairs" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; 
                            Click the "work" tab on the navigation bar that will lead you to the selection of above mentioned files to plot.
                         </li>
                         <li><i class="fa fa-crosshairs" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; 
                            Select the files containing datatypes you want to plot and then click submit at the bottom of the page that will lead you to the selection of datatypes in the selected files.
                         </li>
                          <li><i class="fa fa-crosshairs" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; 
                            Checkbox the Datatypes you want to plot and then click submit at the bottom of the page.
                         </li>
                         <li><i class="fa fa-crosshairs" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; 
                            You are good to view the selected plots.
                         </li>

                         <br>
                        <h4> <strong><i class="fa fa-hand-o-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; FEATURES :</strong></h4><br>
                        <li><i class="fa fa-crosshairs" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; 
                            This tool can adapt to large volume of data , by giving the user to select between ranges of data.
                         </li>

                         <li><i class="fa fa-crosshairs" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; 
                            For greater volume of data, user can view different ranges for selection of data , rather than get confined to a single range.
                         </li>

                         <li><i class="fa fa-crosshairs" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; 
                            There is a clear option , that clears the graph data for large volume of data , so that the user can view only specific selection of range.
                         </li>

                         <li><i class="fa fa-crosshairs" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; 
                            Mix and Match option i.e User will have the option to select different graph data in single graph.
                         </li>

                         <li><i class="fa fa-crosshairs" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; 
                            Finally there is an option to chose the graph between a bar and a pie chart.
                         </li>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
                    

